			               													<description>From the back of the book:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Monsters, Start Your Engines!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Get ready for the Monster Mash, a speed race and battle royale of monstrous proportions. You&amp;rsquo;ll race across 1,000 kilometers of scenic Transylvania. Start by dodging your way past the Rolling Hills, maneuver your way through the Cliffs of Insanity, fend off gnashing piranha in the Scary Swamp, and even visit the grounds of Dracula&amp;rsquo;s Castle. The first monster to reach the Finnish Line (a line hailing from Finland) with their car intact wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this Fudge&amp;trade; System-compatible kart-racing family game, you&amp;rsquo;ll find:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     9 unique racers with their own Perks and Quirks, including: Abominable Snowman, Big Foot, Count Dracula, El Chupacabra, and more.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Guidelines for creating your own racer if you prefer the Do-It-Yourself route.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     9 Power-Ups to help you improve your chances of success, including Garlic Bombs, Piranha Launchers, Invisibility Cloaks, Super Buzz Saws, and more.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     A race course that fights back&amp;mdash;those trees in the Freaky Forest want revenge on woodcutters, but they&amp;rsquo;ll take you instead.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Monster Kart Mayhem is suitable for ages 8 and up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;in 2013 this was introduced as a RPG Geek Adventure Design Contest 2013 entry: Monster Kart Mayhem (RPGG Contest Entry)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
